<p>Heartbit is a program containing a defect analogous to the the 
Heartbleed bug found in OpenSSL.  It is an abstracted version of OpenSSL that
contains many of the essential characteristics of the OpenSSL library along the
code path containing the Heartbleed vulnerability, but is much smaller in size
and easier to operate.
</p>

